Interface DualMap<K,V>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DualHashMap

    public interface DualMap<K,V>
    A DualMap maintains a one-to-one mapping between keys and value. A DualMap object should contain a Map from keys to values and a Map from values to keys. A DualMap cannot contain duplicate keys or duplicate values.
    Author:
    Tom Bylander

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • put

        void put(K key,
       V value)
        Associates the specified value with the specified key in this dual map. After dualmap.put(key, value) is performed, then dualmap.get(key) should return value and dualmap.reverseGet(value) should return key.

        If the dual map previously contained a mapping for the key or the value, the old association(s) should be removed.

        Parameters:
        key - key to be associated with the specified value.
        value - value to be associated with the specified key

      • remove

        void remove(K key,
          V value)
        Removes the mapping from the key to the value from this dual map if it is present. After dualmap.put(key, value) and dualmap.remove(key, value), then dualmap.get(key) should return null and dualmap.reverseGet(value) should return null.
        Parameters:
        key - key whose mapping to value is to be removed
        value - value whose mapping from key is to be removed

      • get

        V get(K key)
        Returns the value that maps from the specified key, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key that maps to the value that should be returned
        Returns:
        the value that maps from the specified key, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the key

      • reverseGet

        K reverseGet(V value)
        Returns the key that maps to the specified value, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the value.
        Parameters:
        value - the value that maps from the key that should be returned
        Returns:
        the key that maps to the specified value, or null if this dual map contains no mapping for the value
